xsd:annotation.xsd:documentation: Defines what type of journal will be printed. (N - normal journals, S - Standard journals and R - recurring journals) If no value is supplied then the default of 'N' will be used.

Defines whether journals that have already been printed should be reprinted. ('N'- No - only journals that have not been printed will be printed, 'Y' -Yes - both journals that have and have not been printed will be printed, O - Only - only journals that have already been printed will be printed). If no value is supplied then a default value of 'N' will be used.
Defines whether the update flag must be set to 'Y" for journals that are printed for the first time. (N - No, Y - Yes). If no value is supplied the the default value of 'N' will be used.
Defines the financial year for which journals should be printed. If no value is supplied the current financial year will be used as a default.
Defines the period selection for journals to be printed. (A - All and S - Single). If no value is passed then the default value of 'A' will be used.
Defines the whether all journals or a range of journals should be printed. (A - all, S-Single,R - range). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'A' will be used.

Defines at what journal number the report should start printing. If no value is supplied a default value of 1 will be used. If 'JournalNumberSelection' is 'A' then whatever value is supplied will be overwritten with a value of 1.

Defines at what journal number the report should stop printing. If no value is supplied a default value of 99999will be used. If 'JournalNumberSelection' is 'A' then whatever value is supplied will be overwritten with a value of 99999.

Indicates whether journals that have/havenot been authorized should be printed. You can also print a combination of both. (B- Both , I - include authorized journals, E - Exclude authorized journals). If no value has been passed then a default value of 'B' will be used.
Defines whether normal journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether provisional journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether user defined journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether inter-company journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether period end adjustments should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether auditors adjustments should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether statistical journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether alternate currency journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether journals that have not been posted should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether journals that have not been put on hold should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether journals that have not been cancelled should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether journals that have been posted should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines the whether all journals or a range of journals should be printed. (A - all,S-Single, R - range). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'A' will be used.

Defines at what journal number the report should starts printing. If no value is supplied a default value of spaces will be used. If 'StandardJournalSelection' is 'A' then whatever value is supplied will be overwritten with a value of spaces.

Defines at what journal number the report should stop printing. If no value is supplied a default value of zzzzz will be used. If 'StandardJournalSelection' is 'A' then whatever value is supplied will be overwritten with a value of zzzzz.
Defines the whether all journals or a range of journals should be printed. (A - all,S-Single, R - range). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'A' will be used.

Defines at what journal number the report should starts printing. If no value is supplied a default value of spaces will be used. If 'RecurringJournalSelection' is 'A' then whatever value is supplied will be overwritten with a value of spaces.

Defines at what journal number the report should stop printing. If no value is supplied a default value of zzzzz will be used. If 'RecurringJournalSelection' is 'A' then whatever value is supplied will be overwritten with a value of zzzzz.

Indicates whether journals that have/havenot been authorized should be printed. You can also print a combination of both. (B- Both , I - include authorized journals, E - Exclude authorized journals). If no value has been passed then a default value of 'B' will be used.
Indicates whether each journal should be printed on a new page. N - No or Y-Yes. If no value has been passed then the default value of 'N' would be used.
Indicates whethertemplate details should be included. N - No or Y-Yes. If no value has been passed then the default value of 'N' would be used.

Defines the period selection for journals to be printed. The period supplied cannot be higher than the number of GL financial periods + 1. If 'PeriodSelection' is 'A' then whatever is supplied in this element will be overwritten with zeroes. If 'PeriodSelection' = 'S' and no value is passed then the current financial period will be used as a default.

Defines whether all journals or a range of journals should be printed. (A - all, S - Single , R - range). Any value supplied will overwrite the value supplied for JournalNumberSelection, FromJournalNumber and ToJournalNumber.

Defines whether all journals or a range of journals should be printed. (A - all, S - Single, R - range). Any value here will overwrite the value supplied for StandardJournalSelection, StandardFrom and StandardTo.

Defines whether all journals or a range of journals should be printed. (A - all, S - Single , R - range). Any value supplied here will overwrite the RecurringJournalSelection, RecurringFrom and RecurringTo.
Defines whether AP Invoice journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether AP Payment journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether AR Invoice journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether AR Cash journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether Asset journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether Cashbook journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether GRN journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether Inventory journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether TPM journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether WIP Labor journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
Defines whether WIP Part Billing journals should be printed. (Y - Yes, N - No). If no value is supplied then the default value of 'Y' will be used.
